name: WHY ARE YOU CRYING WITHOUT HAVING TEARS?
description:
Gazing upon myself, dodging my reflection, and the judgment of my own eyes.. 
Why are you crying? I replied to myself that I had everything..
Why do you cry? It appeared to turn itself into a rhetorical question, so much so that it was the response within itself 
Why do you cry? I reproached with a discrete smile whose contrast on my skin generated  another rumbling question under the disguise of the cloak-and-dagger of my heart.  
Why do you smile? I questioned… to which my reflection answered : 
Because life hasn’t yet given you the tears to truly cry.
